#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn23.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn23.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 23 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 23 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Paṭhamamāravagga → paṭhamavaggo (s1-3) | paṭhamo vaggo (pts1) | paṭhamavagga (c1, c2)
msgctxt "sn23.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamamāravagga "
msgstr "1. About Māra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn23.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Mārasutta "
msgstr "1. About Māra "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.189, sc1
msgctxt "sn23.1:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā rādho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rādho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Rādha went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn23.1:2.1"
msgid "“‘Māro, māro’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of this thing called ‘Māra’. "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.2"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, māro”ti? "
msgstr "How is Māra defined?” "

# NOTE: Using “murder” here I try to maintain the pun.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:2.3"
msgid "“Rūpe kho, rādha, sati māro vā assa māretā vā yo vā pana mīyati. "
msgstr "“When there is form, Rādha, there may be Māra, or the murderer, or the murdered. "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.4"
msgid "Tasmātiha tvaṃ, rādha, rūpaṃ māroti passa, māretāti passa, mīyatīti passa, rogoti passa, gaṇḍoti passa, sallanti passa, aghanti passa, aghabhūtanti passa. "
msgstr "So you should see form as Māra, the murderer, the murdered, the diseased, the abscess, the dart, the misery, the miserable. "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.5"
msgid "Ye naṃ evaṃ passanti te sammā passanti. "
msgstr "Those who see it like this see rightly. "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.6"
msgid "Vedanāya sati … "
msgstr "When there is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.7"
msgid "saññāya sati … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.8"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.9"
msgid "viññāṇe sati māro vā assa māretā vā yo vā pana mīyati. "
msgstr "consciousness, there may be Māra, or the murderer, or the murdered. "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.10"
msgid "Tasmātiha tvaṃ, rādha, viññāṇaṃ māroti passa, māretāti passa, mīyatīti passa, rogoti passa, gaṇḍoti passa, sallanti passa, aghanti passa, aghabhūtanti passa. "
msgstr "So you should see consciousness as Māra, the murderer, the murdered, the diseased, the abscess, the dart, the misery, the miserable. "

msgctxt "sn23.1:2.11"
msgid "Ye naṃ evaṃ passanti, te sammā passantī”ti. "
msgstr "Those who see it like this see rightly.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.1"
msgid "“Sammādassanaṃ pana, bhante, kimatthiyan”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what’s the purpose of seeing rightly?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.2"
msgid "“Sammādassanaṃ kho, rādha, nibbidatthaṃ”. "
msgstr "“Disillusionment is the purpose of seeing rightly.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.3"
msgid "“Nibbidā pana, bhante, kimatthiyā”ti? "
msgstr "“But what’s the purpose of disillusionment?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.4"
msgid "“Nibbidā kho, rādha, virāgatthā”. "
msgstr "“Dispassion is the purpose of disillusionment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.5"
msgid "“Virāgo pana, bhante, kimatthiyo”ti? "
msgstr "“But what’s the purpose of dispassion?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.6"
msgid "“Virāgo kho, rādha, vimuttattho”. "
msgstr "“Freedom is the purpose of dispassion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.7"
msgid "“Vimutti pana, bhante, kimatthiyā”ti? "
msgstr "“But what’s the purpose of freedom?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.8"
msgid "“Vimutti kho, rādha, nibbānatthā”. "
msgstr "“Extinguishment is the purpose of freedom.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.9"
msgid "“Nibbānaṃ pana, bhante, kimatthiyan”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what is the purpose of extinguishment?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Accayāsi → accasarā (bj, s1-3, km) | assa (pts1) | accayā (mr)
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.10"
msgid "“Accayāsi, rādha, pañhaṃ, nāsakkhi pañhassa pariyantaṃ gahetuṃ. "
msgstr "“Your question goes too far, Rādha. You couldn’t figure out the limit of questions. "

# NOTE: For ogadha, BB changed his mind, see his note at AN 3.60.
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.11"
msgid "Nibbānogadhañhi, rādha, brahmacariyaṃ vussati, nibbānaparāyanaṃ nibbānapariyosānan”ti. "
msgstr "For extinguishment is the culmination, destination, and end of the spiritual life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn23.1:3.12"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

